FL,404,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40303
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F403A1774098665
OL,3,CBone found in search for Muriel Mckay
OL,4,Cconfirmed to be non-human
OL,6,FHer lead came following a #1m appeal
OL,7,Ffor information, where the daughter of
OL,8,FPercy Chaplin, the owner of the
OL,9,Ftailor's in the 1960s, came forward.
OL,11,FHayley Frais claims her father
OL,12,Fconfessed on his death bed that he
OL,13,Fbeen associated with criminal gangs
OL,14,Fand thought they had been involved
OL,15,Fwith Mrs McKay's disappearance.
OL,17,FMr Chaplin had employed Arthur Hosein,
OL,18,Fone of the two brothers convicted of
OL,19,FMrs McKay's murder, and suspected that
OL,20,FHosein moved Muriel's body from the
OL,21,Ffarm and hidden it in his shop.
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G3/5
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
